\i\b\fs40 \cf0 Game Objective
\i0\b0\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-2160\ql\qnatural
\cf0 The overall goal of the game is to defeat monsters and gain levels until reaching the end goal. Since you can make your own worlds, the exact way this is accomplished differs from World to World.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0

\i\b\fs40 \cf0 Term Definitions
\i0\b0\fs28 \
Rows and Columns refer to the horizontal and vertical lines of squares making up the World Grid. Floors are stacks of Row/Column Grids. Levels are stacks of Floors. Finally, every World has 2 Layers - the Ground Layer (where Grass, Tile, and other types of ground belong) and the Object Layer (where everything else belongs).\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0

