\f0\i\b\fs40 \cf0 Controls in Battle
\fs36 \

\i0\fs28 Action Points
\fs24 \

\b0\fs28 Moving, as well as some other actions in battle, either by you or the enemies, is limited by available action points. The remaining action points are displayed in the right pane, for the active character. Action points are allowed to go negative, but if this happens your remaining action points will be displayed as 0. This means that actions requiring more than 1 action point can be performed even if you don't have sufficient action points; as long as 1 action point remains, any action requiring action points can be performed.\

\b \
Moving Around
\fs24 \

\b0\fs28 To move, use the arrow keys, the WAXD layout, or the numeric keypad. Pressing 5 or S will cause you to attack yourself; a confirmation prompt will be displayed first, in case you did it accidentally. All movement consumes 1 action point per step.
\fs24 \

\b\fs28 \
Fighting Monsters
\fs24 \

\b0\fs28 To attack the enemy, simply move into them. To run away from battle, move off the edge of the battle arena. Attacking is limited by available attacks, rather than by action points.
\fs24 \

\b\fs28 \
Special Actions
\fs24 \

\b0\fs28 Sometimes, when you attack (and also when the enemy attacks you), different things may occur. One of these is fumbling - if this occurs a random amount of damage will be dealt to the fumbler, based on the power of the weapon held.
\fs24 \

\b\fs28 \
Casting Spells
\fs24 \

\b0\fs28 To cast a spell, assuming you have learned at least one, choose Cast Spell from the Battle menu. The spell selection screen will appear. Select the spell you wish to cast, and click OK (or simply press Return on the keyboard). If you don\'92t know any spells, or don\'92t have enough MP to cast the spell you\'92re trying to cast, a message will be displayed indicating this. Casting spells is limited by a separate spell counter, distinct from the action point counter.
\fs24 \

\b\fs28 \
Stealing Money
\fs24 \

\b0\fs28 To attempt to steal from the enemy, choose Steal Stuff from the Battle menu. If the attempt succeeds, you'll be told how much money you stole. Stealing consumes 6 action points.
\fs24 \

\b\fs28 \
Using Items\

\b0 To use an item, choose Use an Item from the Battle menu. Items do various things when used in battle, from healing you to damaging or incapacitating the enemy. Using an item consumes 6 action points.
\fs24 \

\b\fs28 \
Draining the Enemy
\fs24 \

\b0\fs28 To attempt to drain the enemy's MP, choose Drain MP from the Battle menu. If the attempt succeeds, the enemy loses some MP, and you gain that lost MP. Draining consumes 6 action points.
\fs24 \

\b\fs28 \
Victory! / Defeat!\

\b0 The battle ends when either you or the enemy has run out of HP. If both you and the enemy run out of HP at the same time, the battle is declared a draw, and you get fully healed. If you gain enough XP to level up, a message will be displayed indicating this.
\fs24 \
\

\i\b\fs40 Controls while Shopping
\i0\fs36 \

\fs28 Buying Stuff\

\b0 First select what you wish to buy, and then confirm that you want to buy it when the shopkeeper tells you how much Gold the item or service costs. If you lack the Gold to purchase whatever it was you tried to buy, you\'92ll get a message indicating this. The Weapons and Armor shops give some additional options for selecting exactly what you wish to buy (and, for one-handed weapons, where to equip the purchased item), before presenting a list of items to look through.
\fs24 \

\b\fs28 \
Using the Bank
\fs24 \

\b0\fs28 The Bank, unlike other shops, stores money for later retrieval. It will tell you how much Gold you are carrying, as well as how much you currently have stored. The Bank storage is for all party members together, so it can also be used as a way to transfer gold between members.}